          <mi>d</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>emb</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle d_{\text{emb}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4bf3df2909758ee1d69be67380da3263cfba984e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:4.454ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle d_{\text{emb}}}"/></span>-dimensional vectors.</figcaption></figure>
<p id="mwAoY">The feedforward network (FFN) modules in a transformer are 2-layered <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Feedforward_neural_network" title="Feedforward neural network" id="mwAoc">multilayer perceptrons</a>:<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt266" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{"display":"block"},"body":{"extsrc":"\\mathrm{FFN}(x) = \\phi(xW^{(1)} + b^{(1)})W^{(2)} + b^{(2)}"}}' id="mwAog"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathrm {FFN} (x)=\phi (xW^{(1)}+b^{(1)})W^{(2)}+b^{(2)}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
