  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ed57dd02fd5aafea96a4ee28322e10ca6883249f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:17.471ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="{\displaystyle z_{m}:=x_{m}^{(1)}+ix_{m}^{(2)}}"/></span>, then RoPE encoding is just multiplication by an angle:<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt435" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{"display":"block"},"body":{"extsrc":"\\text{RoPE}\\big(z_m, m\\big) = e^{i m\\theta} z_m\n"}}' id="mwBDc"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block" alttext="{\displaystyle {\text{RoPE}}{\big (}z_{m},m{\big )}=e^{im\theta }z_{m}}">
