        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\tilde {x}}_{1},{\tilde {x}}_{2},{\tilde {x}}_{3},{\tilde {x}}_{4}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d8db060dad8f25abc632d0c847694d10943fefc0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:12.638ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle {\tilde {x}}_{1},{\tilde {x}}_{2},{\tilde {x}}_{3},{\tilde {x}}_{4}}"/></span>. This only takes <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt521" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"4 T_{\\text{GPT-3-small}}"}}' id="mwBOk"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle 4T_{\text{GPT-3-small}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mn>4</mn>
        <msub>
          <mi>T</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>GPT-3-small</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 4T_{\text{GPT-3-small}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f27766b2e3974a6b36c1a34989690d453598eedd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:12.019ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle 4T_{\text{GPT-3-small}}}"/></span>. These tokens are then run through the larger GPT-3 in one go. Suppose that <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt522" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\tilde{x}_1"}}' id="mwBOo"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\tilde {x}}_{1}}">
